text: Burringbar is a small town south-east of Murwillumbah in the Northern Rivers region of New South Wales, Australia. ==Demographics== In the , Burringbar recorded a population of 858 people, 48.6% female and 51.4% male. The median age of the Burringbar population was 41 years, 4 years above the national median of 37. 81.2% of people living in Burringbar were born in Australia. The other top responses for country of birth were England 4.1%, New Zealand 1.5%, Scotland 0.9%, Germany 0.9%, Canada 0.7%. 90.4% of people spoke only English at home; the next most common languages were 1.4% Italian, 0.5% Lithuanian, 0.5% Spanish, 0.3% German, 0.3% Maltese. The novelist Jessica Cole, otherwise known as Jessie Cole, comes from Burringbar, and Burringbar is also the locale for much of her writing. ==References== Category:Suburbs of Tweed Heads, New South Wales
